ANTHRAX, HUMAN - ITALY (LOMBARDY): NOT
**************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
See Also
Anthrax, human - Italy (Lombardy): suspected 20011015.2530
Date: Thu 17 Oct 2002 12:11 PM
From: Antonio Fasanella [edited

Today we have analyzed 13 samples (letters with white powder) by PCR to
reveal the possible presence of DNA of _Bacillus anthracis_. All the
samples gave negative results.
The man from Bergamo is negative to PCR on skin crust and the culture test
is negative.
--
Antonio Fasanella
Istituto zooprophylattico Sperimentalle della Puglia e della Basilicata
Foggia, Italy
<izsfoggia@isnet.it>
[Antonio is responsible for anthrax diagnosis in Italy. Thank you very
much, Antonio, for this authoritative report. - Mod.MHJ
